<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>do someone well • do well by someone</xh5><p> <i>do someone well—</i>1. <i>(of a hotel, etc.)</i> provide a high quality service: Kensington is only a small place, they <u>do you well</u> there, and it’s always full.... <i>2. (followed by Infinitive)</i> be well-advised to act in a particular way: It will <u>do you well</u> to learn these things before you choose a career or job.</p><p> <i>do well by someone—</i>treat a person with loving kindness: Soon after this the boy was transferred to another home, where a childless couple are trying to <u>do well by</u> him.</p><p> <i>See also: do good to someone / do someone good.</i></p> </entry>
